The paper discusses a method for testing and verifying GUI applications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of a black-box model and dynamic analysis suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of parametrized verification, which is a common technique in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research. Finally, the use of machine learning and inference in the black-box model suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
